04/03/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- European Parliament (EP) President Jerzy Buzek on Wednesday (March 3rd) backed Bulgaria's efforts to join the Schengen area and the Eurozone. 
Following a meeting with Prime Minister Boyko Borisov in Sofia, Buzek said he sees Sofia joining Schengen in 2011 and the Eurozone in 2013. 
In addition, Buzek said he hopes Bulgaria will receive EU compensation of 180m euros for shutting down two units of its Kozloduy nuclear power plant. 
(BTA, BGNES, Nova TV, Dnevnik - 03/03/10)
